          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">Conjugate-Cam definition</text><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">: </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">(</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-size:10pt;" translate="true">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">) two </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements" translate="true">2D-Cams</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> on one </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements" translate="true">Part</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, each in contact with a different </text><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">Cam-follower Roller</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> on one different </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Part</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">By definition: the two 2D-Cams move together, and the two Cam-Follower move together with the same motion.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">Conjugate-Cam definition:</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> (formal (Norton) comprise a pair of cams on a common shaft that drive a pair of followers arranged on a common lever or slider that maintain a fixed distance or angle between the (flat) follower surfaces or (roller) centerlines. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;"/></para>
